    <description>In this prospective observational study between March 2013 and March 2017, children (0 to 18 years) with E-ESBL UTI (febrile UTI or cystitis) were enrolled in 24 pediatric departments in France. Clinical and biological characteristics, risk factors of infection of E-ESBL, first and second lines of antibiotic therapies were analyzed. We used the Kaplan-Meier method to estimate the time to apyrexia and length of hospital stay, and Log-rank test to assess equality of survivor functions. We also analyzed the resistance patterns and molecular characterization of ESBL types in the isolates.</description>
